# Security Hardening Rules

## Input Security
- All inputs must use FormRequest validation.
- Reject unknown fields using validatedOnly() concept.

## Authentication
- Use Laravel Sanctum for SPA/API.
- Use Policies for authorization.

## Data Protection
- Never expose internal IDs directly (use UUID or HashId).
- Never return sensitive fields in API responses.

## SQL Injection Protection
- No raw SQL allowed unless parameterized.

## XSS & CSRF
- Blade escaping mandatory {{ }}
- CSRF token required for all POST forms

## File Security
- Validate file type, size, and MIME strictly.
- Store outside public directory.